text: You can catch a glimpse of this serene spot from the lookout deck or while strolling along the promenade. The pier is more like a parking spot along the shore lined with various small boats, creating a picturesque scene thatâ€™s rare in Singapore.

Boat Pier is an unique feature of West Coast Park, not found in other parks.
These boats first moored here when the inhabitants of Palau Sedong, Palau Semakau and other affected Southern Islands were relocated to mainland Singapore.

One of the remaining authentic community spaces in Singapore where indigenous peoples from various Singapore islands, or the people of the sea (Orang Laut) come to practice their crafts. A place that must be preserved in Singapore!
